	<div class="contentwide">
		<h2>Summary:</h2><div class="infobox">You can enter into an Open Borders agreement with another colony. While an Open Borders agreement is in effect, the other colony’s units can enter your territory without automatically triggering war. If the agreement is mutual, either colony’s units can enter the other’s territory freely; however it doesn’t have to be mutual: one colony can grant another Open Borders without automatically receiving it in return.</div>
